sublevels.theory:
Java uses familiar control flow constructs:

**If-else:**
```java
if (score >= 90) { System.out.println("A"); }
else if (score >= 80) { System.out.println("B"); }
else { System.out.println("C"); }
```

**Switch:**
```java
switch (day) {
    case 1: System.out.println("Mon"); break;
    default: System.out.println("Other");
}
```

**Loops:**
- `for (init; condition; update)`
- `while (condition)`
- `do { ... } while (condition);`
- Enhanced for (for-each): `for (int x : array)`

`break` exits a loop, `continue` skips to next iteration.

**Labeled break/continue** — break/continue an outer loop:
```java
outerLoop:
for (int i=0; i<3; i++) {
    for (int j=0; j<3; j++) {
        if (j==1) break outerLoop; // exits outer loop
    }
}
```

**Switch expression (Java 14+):**
```java
String season = switch (month) {
    case 12, 1, 2 -> "Winter";
    case 3, 4, 5  -> "Spring";
    default        -> "Other";
};
```

**Pattern matching switch (Java 21+):**
```java
switch (obj) {
    case Integer i -> "int: " + i;
    case String s  -> "str: " + s;
    default        -> "other";
}
```
